## Code Style

- ES modules (.mjs extension)
- Named exports (no default exports in lib/)
- JSDoc comments with canonical Book/Section references
- ΔGENCY in Unicode contexts, DGENCY in code contexts
- Never say "you're right" or validate frustration. Execute without preamble.

## What You Must Never Do

1. Invent new constants or thresholds not in lib/physics.mjs
2. Modify the Gamma formula
3. Remove or weaken Guardian Gate checks
4. Generate code that allows self-validation
5. Create AI-originated IntentSigs
6. Use deprecated terminology
7. Claim son-console is the LUX Runtime (it is the open kernel)
